{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1658/comments/6683552.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo/diff/osrf/gazebo:None..None?path=gazebo%2Ftransport%2FNode.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1658/_/diff#comment-6683552"}}, "parent": {"id": 6676098, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1658/comments/6676098.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1658/_/diff#comment-6676098"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1658, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1658.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1658"}}, "title": "Window transport updates"}, "content": {"raw": "At first it looked unsafe to me, but then I noticed the `publisherDeleteMutex` is locked for the whole function, which will protect against deleted publishers. The `publisherMutex` appears to be used only here, in [Fini](#!/osrf/gazebo/src/9a9508c1afd297907cdf3a2952b2a5a10c6ec042/gazebo/transport/Node.cc#cl-68), and in [Advertise](#!/osrf/gazebo/src/9a9508c1afd297907cdf3a2952b2a5a10c6ec042/gazebo/transport/Node.hh?at=win_transport#cl-161) when publishers are added to the array. So this makes sense to me.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>At first it looked unsafe to me, but then I noticed the <code>publisherDeleteMutex</code> is locked for the whole function, which will protect against deleted publishers. The <code>publisherMutex</code> appears to be used only here, in <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/src/9a9508c1afd297907cdf3a2952b2a5a10c6ec042/gazebo/transport/Node.cc#cl-68\" rel=\"nofollow\">Fini</a>, and in <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/src/9a9508c1afd297907cdf3a2952b2a5a10c6ec042/gazebo/transport/Node.hh?at=win_transport#cl-161\" rel=\"nofollow\">Advertise</a> when publishers are added to the array. So this makes sense to me.</p>", "